# Visx — Conventions

## Two API Levels

- **`@visx/xychart`** — high-level declarative API with built-in scales, tooltips, themes via React Context. Use for standard cartesian charts (line, bar, area, scatter).
- **Low-level primitives** (`@visx/shape`, `@visx/scale`, `@visx/axis`, etc.) — use when XYChart is too constraining: custom layouts, non-cartesian charts, heavy interactions.

Don't mix levels within one chart. Pick one.

## XYChart Essentials

```tsx
import { XYChart, Axis, Grid, LineSeries, Tooltip } from '@visx/xychart';

<XYChart height={300} xScale={{ type: 'band' }} yScale={{ type: 'linear' }}>
  <Grid columns={false} numTicks={4} />
  <LineSeries dataKey="velocity" data={data} xAccessor={d => d.sprint} yAccessor={d => d.points} />
  <Axis orientation="bottom" />
  <Tooltip
    snapTooltipToDatumX
    showVerticalCrosshair
    showSeriesGlyphs
    renderTooltip={({ tooltipData, colorScale }) => (
      <div style={{ color: colorScale(tooltipData.nearestDatum.key) }}>
        {tooltipData.nearestDatum.key}: {accessors.yAccessor(tooltipData.nearestDatum.datum)}
      </div>
    )}
  />
</XYChart>
```

- `dataKey` is the series identifier — maps to theme colors via `colorScale`.
- `tooltipData.datumByKey` gives nearest datum **per series** (shared tooltips).
- `tooltipData.nearestDatum` is the globally closest datum across all series.

## Animations — Avoid `react-spring`

Use **non-animated** components (`Axis`, `Grid`, `LineSeries` etc.) instead of `Animated*` variants. `Animated*` requires `react-spring` as peer dep — it has React 19 compatibility issues. CSS transitions or `framer-motion` are preferred if animation is needed.

## Responsive

```tsx
import { useParentSize } from '@visx/responsive';

const Chart = () => {
  const { parentRef, width, height } = useParentSize({ debounceTime: 150 });
  return (
    <div ref={parentRef}>
      <XYChart width={width} height={height} ...>
```

- Always wrap charts in `useParentSize` — never hardcode dimensions.
- Set `debounceTime: 150` (default 300 is sluggish).
- **Gotcha**: flex/grid parent without explicit height collapses to 0. Give parent container a CSS height.

## Theming — Integrate with App Palette

```tsx
import { buildChartTheme } from '@visx/xychart';

const chartTheme = buildChartTheme({
  backgroundColor: 'var(--color-surface)',
  colors: ['var(--color-accent)', 'var(--color-secondary)', ...],
  gridColor: 'var(--color-border)',
  gridColorDark: 'var(--color-border-strong)',
  tickLength: 4,
});
```

Export a single shared `chartTheme` from `shared/lib/chart-theme.ts`. Never inline theme objects.

## Low-Level Pattern

```tsx
import { scaleLinear, scaleBand } from '@visx/scale';
import { Group } from '@visx/group';
import { Bar } from '@visx/shape';
import { AxisBottom } from '@visx/axis';

const xScale = scaleBand({ domain: data.map(d => d.label), range: [0, xMax], padding: 0.3 });
const yScale = scaleLinear({ domain: [0, max], range: [yMax, 0] });
```

- Accessor pattern: `const xAccessor = (d: Datum) => d.field` — keep accessors as standalone functions, not inline.
- Compose: `const xPoint = (d: Datum) => xScale(xAccessor(d))` — creates a data→pixel mapper.
- Always define `margin` as `{ top, right, bottom, left }`, compute `xMax = width - margin.left - margin.right`.

## Tooltips (Low-Level)

```tsx
import { useTooltip, TooltipWithBounds } from '@visx/tooltip';

const { showTooltip, hideTooltip, tooltipData, tooltipLeft, tooltipTop, tooltipOpen } = useTooltip<Datum>();
```

- Wrap chart container in a `position: relative` div — tooltip positions are relative to it.
- `TooltipWithBounds` auto-repositions to stay in viewport. Prefer it over raw `Tooltip`.
- `useTooltipInPortal` renders via React portal — use when chart is inside overflow-hidden containers.

## Installed Packages

`@visx/xychart` `@visx/responsive` `@visx/scale` `@visx/shape` `@visx/axis` `@visx/grid` `@visx/group` `@visx/tooltip` `@visx/curve` `@visx/gradient` `@visx/text` `@visx/pattern`

Add more from the visx ecosystem as needed — install individually, never `@visx/visx`.

## FSD Placement

- `shared/lib/chart-theme.ts` — theme config
- `shared/ui/` — reusable chart primitives (e.g., `<ChartContainer>` with responsive wrapper)
- `widgets/` — composed dashboard charts (burndown, velocity, status-distribution)
